{{Infobox writer | image = <!-- [[Freely licenced]] images only. NO SCREEN CAPTURES. Please do not put a fair-use image here, it will be deleted - see [[WP:NONFREE]] --> | birth_name = Charlotte Gordon Cumming | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|2|2|df=y}} | birth_place = Scotland | occupation = [[Musician]] | yearsactive = | spouse = [[Nicholas Evans]] }}
'''Charlotte Gordon Cumming''' (born 2 February 1958) is a Scottish contemporary [[singer-songwriter]] and music producer, daughter of a Scottish clan chief. She wrote the [[Sugababes]] hit "[[Soul Sound]]", nominated for [[MTV]] Best European Single Award 2001. In 2005, the song was covered by [[Indonesia]]n [[singer]] [[Joy Tobing]] on her album ''[[Rise (Joy Tobing album)|Rise]]'' and was recorded by Cumming on her album ''Mindwalking''.
Cumming is influenced by artists such as [[Paul Simon]], [[Peter Gabriel]] and [[Sinéad O'Connor]], though she has developed her own modern blend of Celtic melodies and African rhythms.
She is married to the novelist [[Nicholas Evans]], author of ''The Horse Whisperer''.<ref name = "Times">{{cite news | url = http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/article4660269.ece | last = Sweeney | first = "Charlene | title = Horse Whisperer author, Nicholas Evans, poisoned by wild mushrooms | newspaper = [[The Times]] | date = 3 September 2008 | accessdate = 2009-04-16 | location=London}}.</ref>
In September 2008, while at her brother's estate in Scotland, Cumming, her husband, her brother, and her sister-in-law ate poisonous [[Cortinarius speciosissimus]] mushrooms, which had been misidentified as an edible species.<ref name = "Times" /><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2008/09/02/horse-whisperer-author-po_n_123268.html| author = [[Associated Press]] | title = 'Horse Whisperer' Author Poisoned By Mushrooms | newspaper = [[The Huffington Post]] | date = 2 September 2008 | accessdate = 2009-04-16}}</ref> Several of the group experienced [[kidney failure]] as a result.<ref name="youandyours"/> Cumming remained on [[kidney dialysis]] while seeking [[alternative medicine]] treatments until 2012 when she had a [[kidney transplant]].<ref name="youandyours"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Campsie|first1=Alison|title=Singer Gordon Cumming in 'great shape' following kidney transplant surgery|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/13066858.Singer_Gordon_Cumming_in__great_shape__following_kidney_transplant_surgery/|work=HeraldScotland.com|date=26 Jul 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sanderson|first1=Elizabeth|title=My Horse Whisperer husband accidentally poisoned my brother with deadly mushrooms and we ALL had to have new kidneys|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2224168/My-Horse-Whisperer-husband-accidentally-poisoned-brother-deadly-mushrooms-ALL-new-kidneys.html|work=Daily Mail.com|date=27 October 2012}}</ref>
