'''Elisabeth Hasse''' (1917–1945) was a Nazi SS female supervisor and guard at Auschwitz.<ref name="Hegedu_s2014">{{cite book|author=Anna Molnar Hegedus|title=As The Lilacs Bloomed|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7lDRDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT195|date=1 September 2014|publisher=Azrieli Foundation|isbn=978-1-897470-81-7|pages=195–}}</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=7AiY1QFhJygC&pg=PA180&dq=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi15v6Om9bZAhXjkOAKHcAYDkUQ6AEINzAC#v=onepage&q=Elisabeth%20Hasse%20auschwitz&f=false The Meeting: An Auschwitz Survivor Confronts an Ss Physician - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=r_5VAAAAYAAJ&q=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&dq=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi15v6Om9bZAhXjkOAKHcAYDkUQ6AEIQTAE Auschwitz 1940-1945: central issues in the history of the camp. The ... - Aleksander Lasik - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=guxmAAAAMAAJ&q=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&dq=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi15v6Om9bZAhXjkOAKHcAYDkUQ6AEIVzAI Auschwitz Chronicle 1939-1945 - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> She was known for her brutal treatment of prisoners.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=lgtnAAAAMAAJ&q=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&dq=Elisabeth+Hasse+auschwitz&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi15v6Om9bZAhXjkOAKHcAYDkUQ6AEISjAG Auschwitz, 1940-1945: The prisoners, their life and work - Wacław Długoborski, Franciszek Piper - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Gutman|first1=Israel|last2=Berenbaum|first2=Michael|last3=Museum|first3=United States Holocaust Memorial|title=Anatomy of the Auschwitz Death Camp|date=1998|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=025320884X|page=396|language=en}}</ref> She was one of the eight female guards to be executed.{{cn|date=November 2016}}

