{{more citations needed|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox person |image = |imagesize = | name = Tião Macalé | birth_name = Augusto Temístocles da Silva Costa | birth_date = February 10, 1926 | birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro (city)|Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]] | death_date = October 26, 1993 (aged 67) | death_place = [[São José do Rio Preto]], [[Brazil]] | othername = | occupation = [[Actor]] | yearsactive = }}
'''Augusto Temístocles da Silva Costa''' (February 10, 1926 &ndash; October 26, 1993) known artistically as '''Tião Macalé''', was a Brazilian comedian.
He was born in [[Rio de Janeiro (city)|Rio de Janeiro]]. He is known in Brazil for his role of supporting character in the Brazilian comedic series ''[[Os Trapalhões]]'' in the 1980s and early 1990s, and famous for his catchphrase ''Nojento!'' (Disgusting!) in the series and [[TV commercials]]. He suffered from [[lung diseases]] and died in [[São José do Rio Preto]] in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.globo.com/Videos/Player/Noticias/0,,GIM1363423-7823-ARQUIVO+JN+MORRE+O+COMEDIANTE+TIAO+MACALE,00.html|title=Morre o comediante Tião Macalé (translation:The comedian Tião Macalé dies)|publisher=Globo.com|date= October 26, 1993|accessdate=July 10, 2011|language=pt}}</ref>
